its been a while. a long long while. nothing much of interest with me. i guess just a quick update for all of you who havent heard from me in a while.

i live in nashville TN
with my girlfriend Ashlei
i have my ears pierced
i lost like 100 pounds (skinny)
im an atheist
i love metal (music)

thats all. love you guys

BLAM



betcha didnt expect that.


im 21 friday. horray

wow. its been so long. altho im still a lurker. not much has changed. just me being me. ive been working 10 days straight and im a bit tired. im ready for a day off and that wont come until friday. im trying not to get too depressed but this monotony is starting to take its toll. or maybe ive just reached a new level of depression already where ive just become numb because thats how i feel. i dont really care about anything anymore nothing seems to make a difference to me. my whole world could collapse and i dont think i would blink once. my parents divorce is not really going well. i havent talked to my dad in weeks and every time i talk to my mom with out fail she tries to brain wash me into hating him. and its the most agravating thing. shes got me by the balls with her threats, her blaming me for lack of compassion, and the constant feeding me thoughts of abandonment. her emotional warfare on me is wrong, and theres nothing i can do about it. im an atheist.

<lj-cut text="Gnarls Barlkey is the hottest thing on the block">

Just a Thought - Gnarls Barkley

All i want is your understanding
as in the small lack of affection.
Why is this my life, is almost everybodys question.

And I've tried, everything but suicide,
but its crossed my mind.

I prefer peace,
wouldn't have to have one worldly posession
but essentially Im an animal,
so just what do I do with all the agression?

Well I've tried everything but suicide,
but its crossed my mind.

Life is a one way street ain't it,
If you could paint it, I'd chalk myself going in the right direction,
so i go all the way,
like i really really know what the truth is, im only guessing.

And i tried everything but suicide,
ooh but yes its crossed my mind, just a thought.

It's even dark in the daytime
it's not just good, its great depression.
when i was lost i even found myself, looking in the guns direction

and so i tried, everything but suicide,
and yes its crossed my mind
but im fine.

</lj-cut>

so yeah totally awesome day

First we were headed over to the hot-tub at some apt. complex Then when the hot-tub wasnt heated and dry we went to the "loverslane" of nashville. THEN after that we went back to parkers dorm and he got in the tub to make up for the lack of hot-tub action.

ok im really thinking im going to make this a photo journal because pictures are fun and insteading of typing ill let the picture say it all. and you know what they say pictures say a thousand words. so yeah photojournal now but ill still write too. so yeah fun for everyone

well i worked on my resume. i need to print it out but i think my printer is out of ink. but tomorrow i really really need to go look for a job. ima circle around to a few studios and see whats up there take a tour and network. i might stop by a guitar center or the samash and try to get a job there. i have a lot of bills that need to be paid so i need to motivate myself and get this done. but yeah thats about it

well this is my frist night in nashville and the party has just ended (note the time) crazy party and fun times. i saw a girl who looked exactly like megan and i was all like OMG and long story but i had alot of fun and im so happy i moved up here. i guess thats it for now
peace

well tomorrow morning ill be on the highway heading up to nashville to start my life. its been great knowing all of you and i hope i see you guys around sometime. ill be visiting daphne periodically like on holidays and what not. so everybody wish me luck in finding a jobby and all that jazz. 


that is all

In the year 2006 I resolve to:
Lose all my friends and become a complete geek.

Get your resolution here

well its 2006 and nothing much is going on. im still in canada and its still awesome here. i got a digital camera for christmas so when i get back to alabama ill post some pictures. ill probably post some pictures up on myspace too. (myspace.com/shawnkays) it was great to come here but i think im ready to go back. ill be leaving wednesday and be back thursday. tomorrow we're going to corner brooke to see some family but there are a bunch of mountains over there so hopefully i can go sking or snowboarding or something. but yeah hate to bore you guys for any longer so ill leave now. 

bye

well i made it here in canada nice and safely. it was a fun trip but really stressing. one of our flights was delayed a long time which caused us to almost miss our connecting flight and any other flight going to the same place was booked solid until next week. so we almost spent christmas in a hotel room but all worked out cuz if one flight is delayed that means they all are probably delayed. its snowing like crazy up here and its soo beautiful. oh yeah  not to mention that its freezing cold. but all is well. its great to see my family again. the town that we are in is really small and their mall consists of a walmart and a few other stores. but its reallly cool. i dont know if i want to come back now... j/k.

well thats about it. 
ill keep updating as the days go by.

well im going to canada tomorrow. cant wait to see all my family again and esp. the ones that i havent even met yet. its going to be fun. im going to play in the snow and have snow ball fights and build ice forts and go ice fishing and go snowmobiling and get realllly cold. hopefully i wont get frost bite. but if you guys want me to send you some snow in the mail then just leave your addresses in the comments section. ill be there for christmas and new years. i should be back around january 5th. 


i hope i dont die in a plane crash.
someone call me... preferably a girl
ok so its official im back in daphne for a little while. please call me if you want to hang out or whatever. 251-406-0314

he makes me question everything i thought he stood for. i thought he was a man. hes a coward. how could he do this. he crossed the line. 

ill still always love him tho


i need a smoke

well today was a cool day. we had a competition today where 1 rep from 3 groups got to do a competition and it was my group and two others. and my group chose me to do the competition. well i went up there and kicked its butt. my reward i get to take the day off tomorrow. i was happy. graduation is right around the corner and i cant wait. going to canada for christmas.i need to start packing to come back.

man what a morning. i had lab and we were doing ADR recording for a 2 minute X-MEN II clip and a friend had a lazer pointer and the way the windows are set up is that you can see threw from the inside but the ouside is like a big mirror... so we were shining the laser pointer at this guy who was fixing a light or something and he kept looking around tring to find who was doing that and there was another guy just standing around. so the guy fixing the light got mad finally and like flipped the other guy off and pretty much cussed him out. it was SOOO funny. we all died laughing. we laughed so hard that the microphone picked up our laughing in the iso booth. what a great morning. now i have to study for 3 hours for a quiz i have and i have no idea whats on it. the teacher talks way too fast and he pretty much left me and tons of other students in the dust. so yeah.
yay its my birthday... well i guess its not that exciting.

wow, havnent updated in a while.. i think i might start updating more. but i dont really have anything to talk about. im in session recording right now and i have to book a band for this weekend to record. life is peachy and for the things that arnt peachy i just drown in nicoteen. been doing some hip-hop battles with some people thats been fun. hanging out with lacasse doing some jamming sessions and recording them. i cant wait to get out of fullsail (never thought i would hear myself say that) but its time for me to go to nashville and start  making a living. i still want to do alot of music production but i wouldnt mind getting into post (like tv and film audio) nashville is going to be great cuz some of my good friends are living there and hopefully help me out with some jobbies. still single and still hating it. but i have a feeling once i get a girlfriend that i would regret it. but i need a change in that dept. anyways. i dont think ill be finding one anytime soon because ill only be here for like a month and a week. so ill just wait untill i go to nashville. ill have a good pick up line anyways... "hey im an audio engineer"lol but yeah. im dead broke no money at all and it sucks. i need to start working and making money. im tired of just sitting around and not being able to work. cant wait to go back to daphne for like the 2 weeks that ill be there and see all my old buddies again.

yeah other than those few setbacks than life is peachy.
Take this quiz at QuizGalaxy.com

im broke. anybody wan to donate me some money?... so yeah this month has been hell and i cant wait for it to end. next month should rock, my class is session recording... ill be in the studios for 8hours at a time. that rocks. then the  month after that is audio post production and i get to create sounds for film and music and stuff. then after that im finished with fullsail. ill be back in alabama for like a week or so then ill be moving up to nashville to start my new official life. im really excited. how many people do you know actually are doing what they absolutely love for a living? i cant think of too many except for a few... well i guess im out for now i have lab at 1am to 5am then class 9am to 1pm

oh yeah everybody should check out this band Rasputina its like 3 girls and a guy drummer and the girls have cello's and the guy is the drummer its freaking sweet

peace
i got my truck back... but now im broke

ARRG . my truck broke down and i need to get it fixed and its going to cost me a butt load of money too i bet. 

towing-150 bucks (but the insurance company will pay me back for it)
parts - mabye 50 bucks
diagnostics - 50 bucks
labor - ???? who knows could be alot

i hate it when things break. esp expensive things.

and... 

this girl ive been talking to... she lied to me like 4 times about the same thing but its big and important and i found out shes a shoplifter. go figure. this weekend has been a poopy one. the two days i got off school didnt even phase me.

i found someone to laugh with. i found someone to hang with. i found a really cool girl who is incredably cute. and she likes me. and i like that. this seems to awesome to be real. 

life is so good right now.

and i just got finished watching garden state
right when i think im fed up with the hardcore scene and the music... i turn to the beautiful poetic bliss of bradley hathaway and all is well.

ive had like weird dreams for the past week. really really weird dreams. i have no idea how they corespond to what im thinking or feeling or going threw right now. but i cant really complain because i dont usually remember my dreams if i have them so its kinda cool to have some now. it probably wont last very long.

man this is weird. i havent had a class from 5pm to 9pm in a while so i feel like i should be in school right now but no i gotta wait a couple of hours. so anyways im going to see sam rivers tomorrow night. one of the greatest jazz musicians of all time. 

i need something to do.
the skys are clear... but yet its still raining

well my rap career is starting to take off. i already have one hit out right now... you guys can check it out on myspace. www.myspace.com/mcporkchop i got another hit about to come out either by late tonight or by tomorrow sometime. alls i got to do is record some vocals and das it.

i just finished my final for WS (workstations)and i gotta go back and take my lab test at 5pm here in 2 hours. i think i kicked this tests butt and the lab will be easy as a DOO DOO PIE also. my next class is sound dynamics which is going to be fun cuz its all about setting up for a live enviroment. 

i had a weird dream last night and another one yesterday when i took a nap. it was really really strange. but it was one of those dreams where you wake up and you remember what happend but then five minutes later you cant remember for the life of you what it was about. im concerned that it had some symbolistic meaning behind it but oh well. 

thats about it

i just made you up to hurt myself.


and it worked

god i hate this.. i hate being alone. i guess i kinda gotten used to it by now but if someone wouldnt have said "shawn you really need a girlfriend" then i would be just fine. i can only take it one day at a time.

<lj-cut text="the mobile register article about the dox">

Lake Forest closes teen club over songs
Residents objected to lyrics of music performed at the Dox
Saturday, June 18, 2005
By DAN MURTAUGH
Staff Reporter

DAPHNE -- A popular teenage hangout and concert venue run by three 18-year-olds in Lake Forest has been shut down after residents complained about the content of some of the music played there.

Residents said they were disgusted to learn that bands that played songs with such titles as "Big Bowel Movement in the Little Town of Bethlehem" had played at the Dox teen club.

Prompted by those concerns, the subdivi sion's board of directors voted 4-3 Thursday night to close the club, which is situated in a small building at the end of Country Club Drive, next to Lake Forest's tennis courts and swimming pool. 

It's on a residential street but the closest houses are a few hundred feet away.

More than 9,000 residents live in more than 3,200 homes in the north Daphne development, making Lake Forest Alabama's largest subdivision.

Not all residents were happy with the decision. Some said the Dox was an alcohol-free, smoking-free venue that gave Daphne teenagers a safe place for weekend activities.

Further clouding the issue was the fact that Lake Forest Property Owners Association Board President Mitch Davis is the father of one of the club's managers, Andrew Davis. Sarah Coxwell, another board member, is Mitch Davis' daughter.

The Dox houses video game machines, a snack bar and a stage and sound system for concerts.

Run by recent Daphne High School graduates Andrew Davis, Benji Meloun and Chris Browning, it's about a year old and averages about 100 people at its once- or twice-weekly shows, according to Meloun. (Chris Browning is not the son of Fairhope's police chief, who has the same name.)

The three charged $5 per person to attend the show, and split the proceeds with the bands, according to Davis. 

The shows are advertised as being open to people of all ages. At a recent show, most of the attendees were high school age, with some people in their 20s and one woman -- the mother of a band member -- in her 40s.

At Thursday's property owners association meeting, which a Mobile Register reporter was barred from attending, board members Willie Robison , Ray Drake, B.T. Cocke and Henry Lawson voted to close the facility.

Davis, Coxwell and Ed Kirby voted to keep it open, according to several people present at the meeting. 

Lawson said several residents at Thursday's meeting spoke against the Dox, and none spoke up to defend it.

At the meeting, residents brought several printouts from Web sites of bands that had played the Dox. Included among them was Roman Gabriel Todd's Beast Rising Up Out of the Sea, a band that had played the Dox four times since November and was scheduled to play again in July, according to its Web site.

The band's songs include "Big Bowel Movement in the Little Town of Bethlehem," "Nativity in S---" and others with titles that some may find offensive.

Another band was Fry Cook, which lists among its songs one that refers to male genitalia and another titled "Playing in the Doo Doo."

"The primary reason they were shut down is the bands they were bringing in were violating community standards and rules of decency," Lawson said.

Meloun said those bands aren't representative of all the acts the Dox brings in. He said that the Dox's last show before being shut down featured two Christian bands.

He said he and his friends would have liked the opportunity to respond to the complaints about the vulgar bands and to compromise with the board. 

 "We could get rid of the vulgarity, we could go as far as to ask for a band's lyrics before booking them, but we can't do that if we're shut down," Meloun said Friday.

Mitch Davis said he felt that a lot of the problem was generational.

"I read some of these lyrics, and it's awful stuff," he said. "But in the 1960s, when I was kicking around, people said what Jim Morrison and the Doors wrote was pure trash. 

"People think these kids are swayed by a punk spitting out vulgarity, but they just look at it as another freak show."

Lake Forest had been trying for about 10 years to turn the building into a teen center with little success, according to Mitch Davis. About a year ago, Andrew Davis approached his father and told him he and his two friends wanted to try to run the center, according to Mitch Davis.

Davis referred the three teenagers to Lake Forest General Manager Jake Bodiford, who let them use the building free of charge so long as they maintained the building and kept it smoke-, alcohol- and drug-free, Davis said.

The teenagers brought in video games, snacks and a pool table, Davis said. A few bands got in touch with the kids and asked if they could play at the center, and soon the teens had shows scheduled almost every weekend, Davis said.

Meloun said the first couple of shows only brought in a handful of people, but it has since grown to an average crowd size of 100 for twice-weekly shows.

"It's gotten much bigger than we expected it to," Andrew Davis said.

It also became more problematic.

According to Meloun, residents complained about people speeding, parking in people's front lawns and people making too much noise in the parking lot outside Dox. Lake Forest recently paid for an off-duty police officer to hang around the Dox during concert hours to help keep things in order.

Daphne police Capt. David Wilson said police never had any problems at the Dox that led to an arrest. He said, however, that police were beginning to log calls about the content of music played there.

"We just recently started receiving complaints from neighbors in that area about the number of bands, the type of bands, and the number of young kids coming into that neighborhood," he said. "I believe that some of these same folks started complaining to some of the board members of the Lake Forest Property Owners Association, and they dealt with it."

Meloun said he hopes the Dox saga is not yet over. He said he is trying to gather as many Dox supporters as he can to attend the July 21 board meeting and protest the decision.

"Our whole point is we provide a safe and secure environment for teenagers to have fun," he said. "To my knowledge, it's the only place like that in Daphne, that's one reason we're trying to fight to keep it open."

i think ive reached that breaking point like many of you have about this hardcore music scene. basically ive truely come to realize that hardcore is a fashion now and its not about the music anymore. people are becoming too concerned with their little social groups and their clothes and their whole persona that they are really becoming just like everybody else who they claim to hate. ive become more annoyed at these people who wear their mosh hats and look sad in all these pictures and have ironicly grewsome names for their screen names that almost seem poetic. i seems like some of these people just apply like a "hardcore" formula to their lives and then presto chango like magic they are hardcore. dont get me wrong tho there are still people out there that are true that always have been and always will be. the music is starting to sound the same to me now. all these bands have the same thing in common, breakdowns and little upbeat two step parts with witty little melodys. the bands that i think are taking it to the next level and making something differnt and making new ideas are zao, norma jean, and the chariot. if you listen to these bands their new records are a lot different than what everybody else is playing now. but i guess im not going to talk all this crap and not talk about myself. ill admit it i do kinda fit into this "hardcore" stereotype w/ my hardcore band shirts and some of the music i wrote fit into the hardcore song formula. but the band shirts i do wear i do believe they are true and original and i dont write only hardcore. i also play blues and other genres. my myspace doesnt have some lame poetic yet grewsome tital and my pictures arent of me looking sad or hardcore. arrg. i dont know im just sick of this. yeah i think im done.
